2. Why Java?

Java became popular due to several features:
Platform Independent â†’ Compile once, run anywhere (via JVM).
Object-Oriented â†’ Supports OOP concepts (inheritance, polymorphism, encapsulation, abstraction).
Robust â†’ Strong memory management, exception handling, garbage collection.
Secure â†’ No explicit pointer use, has a security manager for applets.
Multithreaded â†’ Supports concurrent execution of programs.
Distributed â†’ Supports distributed computing with RMI and networking APIs.

